text: New Switzerland is an unincorporated community in Habersham County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== A post office called New Switzerland was established in 1882, and remained in operation until 1889. The community was named after Switzerland, the native land of a large share of the first settlers. ==References== Category:Swiss-American history Category:Unincorporated communities in Habersham County, Georgia Category:Unincorporated communities in Georgia (U.S. state)
title: New Switzerland, Georgia
